SIMPLE: hall-mark
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hall-mark
<hw>Hall"-mark`</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧l"m⟦aum⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The official stamp of the Goldsmiths' Company and other
assay offices, in the United Kingdom, on gold and silver articles,
attesting their purity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence,</specif> <mark>[figuratively]</mark>:
<def>A distinguishing characteristic or characteristics; <as>as, a word
or phrase lacks the <ex>hall-mark</ex> of the best
writers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halloa</ent>⟦br⟧
